 Barazinbar<br />
 Chamber of Mazarbul<br />
 Fortress of Orthanc    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">A pretty basic dwarf deck. This is the deck that I start people on. Younger player especially seem to like it. The only hard rares to get are Durin III, Ring of Fury, and The Binding Ring.<br />
FELLOWSHIP<br />
 Play The Endurances, Weapons, and Artifacts on Gimli and Durin. Don&#39;t heal them unless you are down to the last 2 health on them. Then you can pump them up with the Events. The Disquiets are thier to make sure you aren&#39;t overwhelm. I&#39;ve had Gimli over 30+ strength (without any problem)before. Remember to use the Dwarven Axes ability.<br />
SHADOW<br />
 Play the uruk-hia to make the sites into battlegrounds which give most of them a bonus. Until you get the Suffered Much Loss which changes all of the sites into battlegrounds. Then you can attempt to overwhelm the opponents Ringbearer by using the Brutality. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
